{
  "plan": {
    "root_causes": [
      {
        "hypothesis": "Non-atomic read-check-write: `Ref.get(inflight)` + `.get(key)` + `.set(key, d)` allows two fibers to both see no entry, create separate Deferreds, and the second `.set()` silently overwrites the first, leaving the first fiber's Deferred orphaned.",
        "confidence": "high",
        "evidence": [
          "Lines 99-114 in cache.ts: `const pending = yield* Ref.get(inflight)` returns a reference to the underlying Map, not a snapshot",
          "Two fibers can both read the Map reference before either writes, both see `pending.get(key) === undefined`",
          "Both create a Deferred and call `pending.set(key, d)`, the second set overwrites the first",
          "The first fiber's Deferred is never resolved by `Deferred.done(d, exit)` because `d` is no longer in the map — only the second fiber's exit runs through `Deferred.done`"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "fixes": [
      {
        "id": "fix-atomic-inflight",
        "description": "Replace the non-atomic `Ref.get` + `.get()` + `.set()` pattern with a single `Ref.modify` call that atomically checks for an existing deferred and registers a new one if absent. Follows the established pattern from `acp-next/session.ts`.",
        "files": ["packages/opencode/src/tool/cache.ts"],
        "before": "        // 2. Check inflight dedup\n        const pending = yield* Ref.get(inflight)\n        const existing = pending.get(key)\n        if (existing) {\n          yield* Ref.update(misses, (n) => n + 1)\n          yield* Effect.annotateCurrentSpan({ \"cache.hit\": false, \"cache.dedup\": true })\n          return yield* Deferred.await(existing)\n        }\n\n        // 3. New computation\n        yield* Ref.update(misses, (n) => n + 1)\n        yield* Effect.annotateCurrentSpan({ \"cache.hit\": false, \"cache.dedup\": false })\n        const d = yield* Deferred.make<any>()\n        pending.set(key, d)",
        "after": "        // 2. Check inflight dedup — atomic check-and-register\n        const d = yield* Deferred.make<any>()\n        const existing = yield* Ref.modify(inflight, (pending) => {\n          const found = pending.get(key)\n          if (found) return [found, pending] as const\n          pending.set(key, d)\n          return [undefined, pending] as const\n        })\n        if (existing) {\n          yield* Ref.update(misses, (n) => n + 1)\n          yield* Effect.annotateCurrentSpan({ \"cache.hit\": false, \"cache.dedup\": true })\n          return yield* Deferred.await(existing)\n        }\n\n        // 3. New computation\n        yield* Ref.update(misses, (n) => n + 1)\n        yield* Effect.annotateCurrentSpan({ \"cache.hit\": false, \"cache.dedup\": false })",
        "impact": {
          "affected_files": ["packages/opencode/src/tool/cache.ts"],
          "tests_to_run": ["bun typecheck (packages/opencode)"]
        },
        "risks": [
          "`Deferred.make()` is called eagerly for every getOrCompute call, even cache hits — but it's a lightweight allocation that gets GC'd if unused",
          "The inflight map is mutated in-place inside `Ref.modify` callback — this is safe because `Ref.modify` atomically reads and writes the Ref state, and in-place mutation + returning same reference is the established convention in this file (see: `Ref.update(inflight, (m) => { m.delete(key); return m })`)",
          "If the Deferred is created but not used (dedup hit), it's orphaned — but that's correct behavior: it was never registered in the map so no fiber awaits it, and it will be GC'd"
        ],
        "validation": [
          "Run `bun typecheck` in packages/opencode to confirm no type errors",
          "Manually verify the logical flow: (a) cache hit skips inflight entirely, (b) dedup hit awaits existing deferred, (c) new computation registers and proceeds",
          "The `ensuring` cleanup path (`m.delete(key)`) is unchanged — it still atomically removes the key after computation completes"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "apply_order": ["fix-atomic-inflight"],
    "rollback_plan": "Revert the single edit on packages/opencode/src/tool/cache.ts by reversing the search/replace"
  }
}
